+# Route C Reset25 Runtime Timeout
+
+Date: 2026-04-23
+
+## What Was Verified
+
+After reboot, live DT confirmed the new branch was active:
+
+- `boot_profile=ov5647-dev`
+- node `ov5647_c@36`
+- `serial_c`
+- `cil_settletime = 0`
+- `mclk_khz = 25000`
+- `discontinuous_clk = yes`
+- `reset-gpios` present
+- no `pwdn-gpios`
+
+Manual runtime test:
+
+```bash
+sudo /home/cam/ov5647_driver_codex/scripts/run_manual_insmod_diag.sh full-delay-dump
+sudo /home/cam/ov5647_driver_codex/scripts/run_manual_single_frame_rtcpu_trace.sh
+```
+
+## What Changed
+
+- `parse_dt` now reports:
+  - `reset_gpio=486`
+  - `pwdn_gpio=-1`
+- driver logs show:
+  - `ov5647_apply_pwdn_gpio: ... no pwdn GPIO`
+- this confirms the reset-only semantics branch is really active.
+
+## What Did Not Change
+
+- probe succeeds
+- chip-id `0x5647` is read
+- `VIDIOC_STREAMON` returns success
+- raw output stays `0 bytes`
+- VI still logs repeated `uncorr_err: request timed out after 2500 ms`
+- RTCPU/NVCSI trace still shows no SOF/EOF or receiver interrupt events
+
+## Important Caveat
+
+This was not yet a full electrical `25 MHz` test.
+
+Although live DT says `mclk_khz = 25000`, the runtime log still shows:
+
+- `mclk enabled rate=24000000`
+
+So the next narrow follow-up is:
+
+- same route-C reset-only branch
+- but force `mclk_override_hz=25000000`
+
+## Interpretation
+
+The route-C reset-only branch itself did not restore SOF.
+
+But it did reveal one remaining software-only gap:
+
+- the branch has not yet been tested with a real forced `25 MHz` MCLK at runtime.
